Rosy Meurer, the wife to Nollywood actress Tonto Dikeh’s ex-husband, Olakunle Churchill, has responded to critics in regards to posting and wishing her step-son a happy birthday on her Instagram page. According to the Nollywood actress in a post via her Instagram post on Sunday, she didn’t mean her harm with her post despite not having a good relationship with her step-son’s mom. She wrote, “At the end of the day, I know that I am a good person,” she wrote in the caption. Buhari Demands Return Of More Nigeria’s Artefacts From Abroad 2023: South-South Lawmakers Endorse Yahaya Bello For President “I am far from perfect, but my intentions are good; my heart is pure, and I love with everything I have. Because of these things, I am worth it. Always have been, always will be.” Recall that Tonto had accused Rosy Meurer of having an affair with her ex-husband, while she was still married to him. Meurer is currently married to Churchill and has welcomed a son with her husband.